        <div class="row" style="margin-top: 30px;">
            <div class="col-md-5">
                <h3 class="text-info">Findings</h3>
                <br>
                <p>In this project, we successfully visualize and show farmlamds in Ibadan, and the predicted
                    areas likely to be affected by flood in 5 years time. Below we list some of our findings and
                    observations.
                    <ul>
                        <li>The city of Ibadan is subceptible to flood as there are lots of waterways in the area.</li>
                        <li>Using the geospatial data, we discovered that 357 farmlands out of 876 farmlands in Ibadan
                            will be affected by the flood if there is no intervention.</li>
                        <li>If corrective and preventive measures are taken against the flood, the number of affected
                            farmland will be reduced by 82.6%, which is saving 295 farmlands.</li>
                        <li>128 farmlands in Akinyele local government will be affected by the flood. This will be
                            the highest record followed closely by Oluyole LGA</li>
                        <li>Commercial farms in Ibadan will be most affected before and after an intervention.

                        </li>


                    </ul>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-5">
                <h3 class="text-info">Recommendations</h3>
                <br>
                <p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>A contingency plan is seriously needed in the city of Ibadan, Nigeria. This can be achieved
                            through following the four-phased flood disaster management techniques which are mitigation,
                            preparation, response and recovery. Since we have successfully achieved the first phase
                            which is
                            the identification, we can move to the next phases.
                </p>
                <li>There should be a focus on the disaster preparedness in the rural communities, and the people
                    should be well trained and informed on flood disaster risks and management.
                    Regular inspections on adherence to land policies by the ministry of lands and environment
                    should be carried out in areas around Ibadan that have lots of natural watercourses.</li>
                <li>An effective information or warning system can be built close to farmlands identified and
                    warning signals should be sent to farmers with land prone to flooding.</li>
                <li>Good drainage systems should be built in strategic areas to allow easy flow of water thereby
                    reducing flooding.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
